        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 1:36PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 136 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Patton Creek, or over Hoover, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Joe Tucker Park, Riverchase, Ballantrae, Patton Creek, Shannon, Oak
Mountain State Park, Hoover Metropolitan Stadium, Hoover Veterans
Park, Saddle Lake Farms, Ross Bridge, Bounds Lake, Bluff Park,
Hoover, Helena, Chelsea, Pelham, Riverchase Galleria, Lake Cyrus, Oak
Mountain Amphitheater, and Indian Springs Village.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
